quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  28,51,We have continuously conveyed the Word to them that they might take heed
  28,52,"Those to whom We gave the Book before [are bound to] believe it"
  28,53,"When it is recited to them, they say, \"We believe in it. It is the Truth from our Lord. We had devoted ourselves to God even before this came to us"
  28,54,"They will be given their reward twice for what they patiently endured, and [because] they ward off evil with good, and give from what we have provided for them"
  28,55,"When they hear worthless talk, they turn away from it and say, \"We have our deeds, and you have your deeds. Peace be with you; we do not seek the company of the ignorant"
  28,56,"You [Prophet] cannot guide [to the Truth] whom you love, but God guides him who wants to be guided. And He knows best those who are guided"
  28,57,"They say, \"If we were to follow the guidance with you, we would be torn from our land.\" Have we not established for them a safe sanctuary, to which are brought all kind of fruits, as provisions from Us? But most of them do not understand"
  28,58,"How many towns have We destroyed which lived in ease and plenty but were ungrateful? Here are their dwellings, virtually uninhabited since their time. We have inherited them"
  28,59,"Your Lord never destroys cities unless He [first] sends a messenger in their midst reciting Our verses, nor would We destroy cities unless their inhabitants were evil"
  28,60,"[People] whatever you are given is only for the [passing] enjoyment and vanity of this life, but what is with God is better and more lasting. Will you not, then, use reason"
  28,61,"Is the one who sees the fulfillment of the good promise We gave him [about the Hereafter] like the one We provided with worldly enjoyment [but] who, on the Day of Resurrection, is summoned [for punishment]"
  28,62,"On that Day, He will call them and say, \"Where are My partners whom you used to claim"
  28,63,"Those against whom the charge will be proved will say, \"Our Lord, these are the people we led astray, just as we, too, were led astray. We declare our innocence to You; it was not us they were worshipping"
  28,64,"It will be said to them, \"Call those 'partners.' \" They will call them, but they will not respond to them, and they will see the punishment [that awaits]. If only they had followed Our guidance"
  28,65,"On that day He will call them and say, \"How did you respond to My Messengers"
  28,66,"All their usual arguments will be of no use to them that Day, and they will not [be able to] ask one another"
  28,67,"As for the one who has repented, believed, and done righteous deeds, he can hope that to be counted among the successful"
  28,68,Your Lord creates whatever He wills and chooses; The choice is never theirs. May God be exalted in His Glory and far above all they associate with Him
  28,69,Your Lord knows what their hearts conceal and what they declare
  28,70,"He is God; there is no god except Him. [All] praise belongs to Him in this world and the next. The judgment is His, and to Him you will be returned"
  28,71,"Say, \"Just think, if God were to make the night continuous for you until the Day of Resurrection, what god other than God could bring you light? Will you not listen"
  28,72,"Say, \"Just think, what if God should make daylight continuous for you until the Day of Resurrection, what god other than God could bring you the night in which to rest? Will you not see"
  28,73,"But, out of His mercy, He made the night and the day for you so that you may rest, and seek from His favor, and perhaps give thanks"
  28,74,"On the Day He will call them and say, \"Where are those you used to claim as My partners"
  28,75,"We will pull out a witness from every nation and say, \"Produce your evidence.\" They will then know that the Truth belongs to God alone, and [the gods] they have invented have forsaken them"